<TITLE> Barca's Toure and Iniesta out for two weeks with injuries </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MADRID, March 23 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Barcelona midfielders Yaya Toure and Andres Iniesta will be out of action for up to 15 days with thigh injuries picked up in the side's 6-0 Primera Liga win over Malaga, the league leaders said on Sunday. Toure had to be substituted in the 25th minute at the Nou Camp after tearing a muscle in his right thigh, and Iniesta was taken off in the second half with a similar problem, the club's medical services reported. Both players were due to be on international duty next week  Toure with Ivory Coast and Iniesta with European champions Spain. Barca also said that a third midfielder Xavi was substituted with an Achilles tendon problem, but that he would be joining up with the Spain squad as planned
